FBIS4-771 "drafr073_c_94014" FBIS-AFR-94-073 Daily Report 13 Apr 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA IEC Lists International Election Observers IEC Lists International Election Observers MB1304154394 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1437 GMT 13 Apr 94 MB1304154394 Johannesburg SAPA English BFN [Statement issued by the Independent Electoral Commission on 13 April on the SAPA PR Wire Service] [Text] A total of 77 international organisations and 26 local organisations have been accredited by the monitoring directorate, according to Lucia Mtshali of the Department of Accreditation and Logistics at national office. This does not include the inter-governmental organisations like the United Nations, the OAU and the European Community. The deadline for the accredition of international and local organisations for the purpose of observing the elections, expired on March 27. A few late applications have been accepted. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |International NGOs | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Organisation |Observers [figures as received] | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |1. Pollwatch Africa (Botswana) |17 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |2. Oxfam Canada (Canada) |35 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |3. Canadian Labour Congress (Canada) |25 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |4. Forum Sudliches Africa (Fosa) (Ger-|3 | |many) | | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |5. Awepa (Netherlands) |250 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |6. Catholic Church |41 | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |7. Ecumenical Monitoring Programme in |216 | |South Africa (EMPSA) | | 